Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and mixed woodland; conifer plantations; wooded river and lake sides; common in carr woodland; heathland; wetlands including fen, bog, wet meadows, grassland with pingo pools, sedge beds
Typha latifolia
and marsh; former gravel workings; calcareous grassland; ancient parkland; dunes. Reared from the fungus
Laetiporus sulphureus
. vâ€“x.
